Friday morning brought tragedy after a Grove End resident was found with a gunshot wound. Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) received a call from a resident in Grove End reporting a domestic dispute followed by a gunshot. “Reaction officers and Rusa paramedics arrived on scene and discovered that a 42-year-old male had suffered a self-inflicted gunshot wound. He was pronounced deceased,” said Rusa head, Prem Balram. Captain Louise Naidoo, Phoenix SAPS communications officer said that an inquest docket has been opened at the station. “There was an argument in the household. Family members claim that they attempted to speak to the victim who locked himself in the room. “They further alleged that they begged him to open the door but he failed to respond. The family members reported that they heard a loud bang and proceeded to break down the door.The family members found the victim in a pool of blood on the bed with a silver pistol in his hand and a gunshot wound to his head,” said Naidoo.